Durban - Professional surfer and diving skipper Bradley Mommsen had no idea what he was about to capture when he flew his drone above surfers near Scottburgh main beach last month.
The 37-year-old Scottburgh man said his intention was to shoot South Africa’s “golden surfer boy” Jordan Michael Smith on June 19.

“I knew he was surfing out there that morning so before I paddled out to surf, I wanted to see if I could catch a few of his waves on my drone before going surfing myself,” said Mommsen.

After changing the angle of his drone, Mommsen said the glare from the sun was “removed from the shot and I could see right through the water to the sea bed”.

