Mommsen said he wasn’t surprised by the shark sighting because it is sardine season and there were a lot of sardine pockets passing by further out to sea.

“I didn’t really think anything of it, just that I spotted sharks and they were swimming around the surfers. They weren’t aggressive at all, they were just inquisitive,” he said.

Mommsen believes that sharks are mysterious creatures that we know very little about. “As you can tell from the footage, these aren’t the misunderstood scenes from Jaws. Movies and marketing have a way of planting seeds of fear in the minds of individuals and, ultimately, people live in fear of these creatures,” he said.








