Mommsen hopes that his footage will contribute to shark awareness and called on experts to explain the activity seen in the footage.
Matt Dicken, from the KwaZulu-Natal Sharks Board, confirmed that there had been increased shark activity along the coast. However, he said no incidents had been reported.

Dicken explained that the increased shark activity noted, especially sightings of copper sharks, is sardine-run related and that all shark nets from Durban to Port Edward have been removed.








